ownedComment.body: OntoUML is a UML Profile whose elements represent finer-grained distinctions between different kinds of types and encompasses a set of constraints defining the admissible relations between these elements. It is particularly suited for modeling domain ontologies.

properties.documentation: NEMO (Núcleo de Estudos em Modelagem Conceitual e Ontologias) is a research group devoted to investigating the application of domain and foundational ontologies as well as ontology-based techniques in various aspects of conceptual modeling such as information modeling, enterprise modeling, agent-based systems and semantic web.

OntoUML is a UML Profile whose elements represent finer-grained distinctions between different kinds of types and encompasses a set of constraints defining the admissible relations between these elements. It is particularly suited for modeling domain ontologies.

properties.alias: (Guizzardi G. 2005 Ontological Foundations for Structural Conceptual Models p.360)
